  "contents": "<article>\n  <div class=\"breadcrumb-container\">\n    <div class=\"breadcrumb\">\n      <script type=\"application/ld+json\">\n        {\n          \"@context\": \"http://schema.org\",\n          \"@type\": \"BreadcrumbList\",\n          \"itemListElement\": [\n            { \"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 1, \"item\": { \"@id\": \"https://angular.io/api\", \"name\": \"API\" } },\n            { \"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 2, \"item\": { \"@id\": \"https://angular.io/api/core\", \"name\": \"@angular/core\" } },\n            { \"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 3, \"item\": { \"@id\": \"https://angular.io/api/core/model\", \"name\": \"model\" } }\n          ]\n        }\n      </script>\n        <a href=\"/api\">API</a> > <a href=\"api/core\">@angular/core</a>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"github-links\">\n  <a href=\"https://github.com/angular/angular/tree/17.3.12/packages/core/src/authoring/model/model.ts#L105-L110\" aria-label=\"View Source\" title=\"View Source\"><i class=\"material-icons\" aria-hidden=\"true\" role=\"img\">code</i></a>\n</div>\n  </div>\n  <header class=\"api-header\">\n    <h1 id=\"model\">model<a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"api/core/model#model\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a></h1>\n    <label class=\"api-type-label const\">const</label>\n    <label class=\"api-status-label dev-preview\" title=\"This API is in Developer Preview\">\n      <a href=\"guide/releases#developer-preview\">developer preview</a>\n    </label>\n    \n  </header>\n  <aio-toc class=\"embedded\"></aio-toc>\n\n  <div class=\"api-body\">\n  <section class=\"short-description\">\n    <p><code><a href=\"api/core/model\" class=\"code-anchor\">model</a></code> declares a writeable signal that is exposed as an input/output\npair on the containing directive.</p>\n\n    <p><a href=\"api/core/model#description\">See more...</a></p>\n  </section>\n  <code-example language=\"ts\" hidecopy=\"true\" class=\"no-box api-heading\">\n  const <a href=\"api/core/model\" class=\"code-anchor\">model</a>: <a href=\"api/core/ModelFunction\" class=\"code-anchor\">ModelFunction</a>;\n  </code-example>\n\n  \n<section class=\"description\">\n  <h2 id=\"description\">Description<a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"api/core/model#description\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a></h2>\n  <p>The input name is taken either from the class member or from the <code>alias</code> option.\nThe output name is generated by taking the input name and appending <code>Change</code>.</p>\n  <p>Further information is available in the <a href=\"api/core/model#usage-notes\">Usage Notes...</a></p>\n</section>\n\n<section class=\"usage-notes\">\n  <h2 id=\"usage-notes\">Usage notes<a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"api/core/model#usage-notes\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a></h2>\n  <p>To use <code><a href=\"api/core/model\" class=\"code-anchor\">model</a>()</code>, import the function from <code>@angular/core</code>.</p>\n<code-example>\nimport {<a href=\"api/core/model\" class=\"code-anchor\">model</a>} from '@angular/core`;\n</code-example>\n<p>Inside your component, introduce a new class member and initialize\nit with a call to <code><a href=\"api/core/model\" class=\"code-anchor\">model</a></code> or <code>model.required</code>.</p>\n<code-example language=\"ts\">\n@<a href=\"api/core/Directive\" class=\"code-anchor\">Directive</a>({\n  ...\n})\nexport class MyDir {\n  firstName = <a href=\"api/core/model\" class=\"code-anchor\">model</a>&#x3C;string>();            // <a href=\"api/core/ModelSignal\" class=\"code-anchor\">ModelSignal</a>&#x3C;string|undefined>\n  lastName  = model.required&#x3C;string>();   // <a href=\"api/core/ModelSignal\" class=\"code-anchor\">ModelSignal</a>&#x3C;string>\n  age       = <a href=\"api/core/model\" class=\"code-anchor\">model</a>(0);                   // <a href=\"api/core/ModelSignal\" class=\"code-anchor\">ModelSignal</a>&#x3C;number>\n}\n</code-example>\n<p>Inside your component template, you can display the value of a <code><a href=\"api/core/model\" class=\"code-anchor\">model</a></code>\nby calling the signal.</p>\n<code-example language=\"html\">\n&#x3C;span>{{firstName()}}&#x3C;/span>\n</code-example>\n<p>Updating the <code><a href=\"api/core/model\" class=\"code-anchor\">model</a></code> is equivalent to updating a writable signal.</p>\n<code-example language=\"ts\">\nupdateName(newFirstName: string): void {\n  this.firstName.set(newFirstName);\n}\n</code-example>\n\n</section></div>\n</article>\n\n<!-- links to this doc:\n - api/core\n - api/core/ModelFunction\n - api/forms/FormControlDirective\n - api/forms/FormControlName\n - api/forms/NgModel\n - guide/form-validation\n - guide/forms\n - guide/lazy-loading-ngmodules\n - guide/model-inputs\n - guide/testing-components-scenarios\n - guide/upgrade\n-->\n<!-- links from this doc:\n - /api\n - api/core\n - api/core/Directive\n - api/core/ModelFunction\n - api/core/ModelSignal\n - api/core/model#description\n - api/core/model#model\n - api/core/model#usage-notes\n - guide/releases#developer-preview\n - https://github.com/angular/angular/tree/17.3.12/packages/core/src/authoring/model/model.ts#L105-L110\n-->"
